  "time_ut": 1662000248,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0dad\u0dc0\u0daf\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0da7\u0dad\u0dca \u0dad\u0daf \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dc3\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "More heavy rain",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to the Department of Meteorology, rain or thundershowers will occur in many areas today (1) due to the turbulent condition in the lower atmosphere near Sri Lanka.",
        "Accordingly, a spokesman for the department said that there will be occasional rain or thundershowers in the Western, Sabaragamuwa, Central, North-Western and Northern provinces, as well as in the Galle, Matara and Anuradhapura districts.",
        "He said that some places in Western, Sabaragamuwa, Central, North-West and Northern provinces will experience heavy rains of more than 75 mm, while in Uva and Nagenegira provinces there will be rains or thunderstorms in the evening or at night.",
        "The Department of Meteorology also informs the people to take action to avoid accidents as lightning accidents and temporary strong winds may occur along with thunder showers.",
        "(Diana Udayangani) According to the Department of Meteorology, rain or thundershowers will occur in many areas today (1) due to the disturbance in the lower atmosphere near Sri Lanka. Accordingly, a spokesman for the department said that there will be occasional rain or thundershowers in the Western, Sabaragamuwa, Central, North-Western and Northern provinces, as well as in the Galle, Matara and Anuradhapura districts. He said that some places in Western, Sabaragamuwa, Central, North-West and Northern provinces will experience heavy rains of more than 75 mm, while in Uva and Nagenegira provinces there will be rains or thunderstorms in the evening or at night. The Department of Meteorology also informs the people to take action to avoid accidents as lightning accidents and temporary strong winds may occur along with thunder showers."
      ],
